            "Freeze occurs when the air temperature is at 32 Grad Fahrenheidt or O grad Celsius or below overa widespread area for a cl imatologically significant perio d of time. Use of the term is usually rest ri ct ed to advect ive situatio ns or to occasions when wind or other conditio ns prevent frost . Frost and freeze are part icularl y damaging during the cr op growing season."@en ;
        skos:notation "frostFreeze" ;
